CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 22, 1958, page 42, reads: "Tubman Guild Terrace House - Enjoying the peace and quite of the Harriet Tubman Guild's Terrace House are Mrs. Nafeesha Zayne and Mrs. Lillie Woods, patients; Mrs. Calvin Barthless, chairman of the guild's publicity and program committee, and Mrs. Louise C. Smith, supervisor of Terrace House. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Harriet Tubman Terrace House for Convalescent Women and Girls patients, Nafeesha Zayne and Lillie Woods, chairman of publicity, Mrs. Calvin Barthless, and supervisor, Louise C. Smith wearing nurse uniform, seated in room with mantle, piano, television, and checkered floor
